> If you're looking for a recipe that'll satisfy your whole team, chili is a sure bet. In this version, we're keeping things simmering with ground beef, borlotti beans, poblano peppers, and our special Mexican spice blend, which has just the tiniest bit of heat. It's mild enough for your kids to gobble up but has plenty of flavor to satisfy the adults—just break out the hot sauce if you like it scorching!

Wash and dry all produce. Trim, then thinly slice @Scallions{4%unit}, keeping greens and whites separate. Mince @Garlic{4%clove}. Core and seed @Poblano Pepper{2%unit}, then cut into ½-inch squares. Drain and rinse @Borlotti Beans{26.8%ounce}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, tall-sided pan over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Beef{22%ounce}, breaking up meat into pieces. Cook, tossing occasionally, until browned at the edges and no longer pink, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Remove from pan with a #slotted spoon{} and set aside.

Remove pan from heat and carefully pour out and discard any excess grease left by beef. Return to medium-high heat and add scallion whites, poblanos, and garlic. Cook, tossing, until lightly browned and softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add @Mexican Spice Blend{2%tablespoon} to pan and toss to coat veggies. Cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add @Veggie Stock Concentrate{2%unit}, beans, @Crushed Tomatoes{27.52%ounce}, beef, and @water{2%cups} to pan and stir to combine. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and let simmer until thick and stew-like, about ~{10%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide chili between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @Cheddar Cheese{1%cup} and scallion greens. Dollop with @Sour Cream{8%tablespoon} and serve.